author: The Columbus Dispatch
title: High-school football | Ohio Capital Conference roundup: Grove City wins on late field goal
text:
Grove City 10, Gahanna 7:   Jonah Monhemius kicked a 36-yard field with 1:30 left, and Grove City (3-5, 2-3) upset host Gahanna (6-2, 4-1) in the OCC Ohio.  
Kent Johnson put Gahanna ahead in the third quarter on a 22-yard touchdown run. One minute later, Eric Spohn returned a Gahanna fumble for a score to tie it at 7.  
Grove City, which held the ball for more than 32 minutes, gained just 145 yards, with Jeremy Ford rushing for 101 yards.  

Olentangy Orange 27, Franklin Heights 20:   Tyler Lichter scored three touchdowns, including two in the fourth quarter, to lift Olentangy Orange (2-6, 2-3) over visiting Franklin Heights (0-7, 0-4) in the OCC Captial. 
Lichter, who finished with 154 yards, scored on an 8-yard run with 8:43 remaining and a 1-yard run with 4:47 left. Blake Skuratowicz scored Orange’s first TD, a 1-yard run in the second quarter.  
Brenden Knox led Franklin Heights with 186 yards rushing and a touchdown and Seth Dawkins had a 1-yard TD run to give the Falcons a 20-13 lead in the third quarter. Dylan Akers completed 13 of 27 passes for 121 yards and one TD for the Falcons, who outgained Orange by 60 yards.  

Delaware 34, Mount Vernon 29:   Cullen Moore rushed for 211 yards and three touchdowns, including the winning score with a 36-yard run in the fourth quarter, and Delaware (4-4, 2-3) beat host Mount Vernon (5-3, 1-4) in the OCC Capital.  
Moore had 20 carries and scored on runs of 1, 37 and 36 
Nate Davis caught six passes for 131 yards and returned two kickoffs for touchdowns, both from 84 yards out, and quarterback Mason Williams threw for 195 yards and added 50 rushing for Mount Vernon.  

New Albany 29, Big Walnut 7: Brandon DeHass rushed for 117 yards and scored three touchdowns to lead New Albany (5-3, 4-1) past host Big Walnut (2-6, 1-4) in the OCC Capital.  
Casey Horch completed 8 of 15 passes for 131 yards and two scores for New Albany. Sam Blaha caught one TD for 33 yards while DeHass caught the other TD for 16 yards.  
DeHass also scored on runs of 50 and 12 yards.  
Evan Garcia rushed for 132 yards and David Hunt scored on a 1-yard TD run for Big Walnut.  

Dublin Jerome 45, Canal Winchester 13: Zach Hazlett rushed for two touchdowns and passed for another, and Dublin Jerome (4-4, 4-1) used a 21-0 start to roll past visiting Canal Winchester (0-8, 0-5) in the OCC Cardinal Division.  
Hazlett completed 15 of 23 passes for 144 yards and Ryan Prochko rushed for 133 yards and one TD for the Celtics.  

Hilliard Darby 28, Dublin Scioto 10: Nick Powers rushed for 143 yards and scored all four touchdowns for Hilliard Darby (8-0, 5-0) in an OCC Cardinal victory over host Dublin Scioto (2-6, 1-4). 

Hilliard Bradley 35, Westerville North 0: Will Phillis threw three second-quarter touchdown passes and Hilliard Bradley (5-3, 3-2) defeated host Westerville North (0-8, 0-5) in an OCC Cardinal game. Phillis completed 14 of 20 passes for 230 yards and connected with Derek Dunnagan 10 times for 176 yards and a score. 

Westerville Central 42, Westerville South 7: Benny Snell rushed for 210 yards and two touchdowns, and Westerville Central (8-0, 5-0) returned two interceptions for TDs to beat host Westerville South (3-5, 2-3) in the OCC Cardinal.  
Daniel Rucker returned an interception 37 yards for a score and Andrew Wallace ran back an interception 47 yards for another score.  
Jaelen Gill rushed for 148 yards and one TD for South.  

Central Crossing 49, Thomas Worthington 12:   Colter Bass had three rushing touchdowns, Deric Williamson accounted for three more and Central Crossing (5-3, 3-2) cruised to an OCC Central win over visiting Thomas Worthington (1-7, 0-5). Bass had 111 yards rushing and scored from 16 yards to give the Comets a 21-6 lead in the second quarter. Williamson, who had 227 yards passing, ran in a pair of short TD runs and capped the night with a 32-yard TD pass to Koran Montague.  

Dublin Coffman 38, Westland 13:  Gunnar Hoak completed 22 of 36 passes for 360 yards and one TD for Dublin Coffman (5-3, 3-2) in an OCC Central win over host Westland (4-4, 2-3).  
Eric Bradford caught nine passes for 183 yards and Brady Rothgeb caught seven passes for 94 yards and one TD. Casey Kirk rushed for 122 yards and one TD while Joe Kendrick also scored on two short runs for Coffman.  
Abdul Diallo returned a fumble 69 yards for a TD for Westland, which gained just 149 yards. 

Upper Arlington 20, Marysville 7:   Cole Kaparos had 161 yards rushing to pace Upper Arlington (6-2, 3-2) to an OCC Central win over visiting Marysville (2-6, 1-4). Danny Logan added 111 yards rushing and 52 receiving and Christian Mathews capped the Golden Bears’ scoring with a 48-yard touchdown run in the fourth quarter. 

Pickerington North 28, Groveport 14:   Host Pickerington North (4-4, 2-3) broke a 14-14 halftime tie with two third-quarter touchdowns to defeat Groveport (5-3, 2-3) in the OCC Ohio. Bralen Wilson rushed for 82 yards and two touchdowns, including a 5-yard TD run that put the Panthers ahead to stay. North quarterback Michael Lowery completed 12 of 19 passes for 159 yards and a score. 

Pickerington Central 42, Newark 14:   Noah Burk rushed for 159 yards on 10 carries and scored once as Pickerington Central (6-2, 4-1) moved into a first-place tie in the OCC Ohio with a victory over visiting Newark (0-8, 0-5).  
Burk had an 80-yard run to start the scoring. Terry Simuel scored once rushing and receiving and Seth Currens threw two TDs passes for the Tigers.
